---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 61
  - Title: Ecclesiasticus
    Location: V 4
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=God’s Justice
Commentary: |
  Both this presumption on the one hand and despair (as in the citations
  [tagged Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=God's Mercy]) on the other are
  classed as ‘sins against the Holy Ghost’.
---
Say not： I have sinned, and what harm hath befallen me? for the Most High is
a patient rewarder.
